<br>
This means that I have a whole bag full of Robes of the Cyclone (AC 8, DEX 2, INT 5, sv fire 3, sv cold 4, sv magic 3, wt 0.0, tiny, ALL; NEC, WIZ, MAG, ENC, off white, looks like a damask or gossamer robe) and Robes of Burnishing (AC 9, CHA 2, INT 6, AGI 2, HP 5, mana 5, sv disease 6, sv poison 6, wt 0.0, tiny, ALL; NEC, WIZ, MAG, ENC; deep blue, almost black, looks like a blackened crystalline robe without the green highlights).<br>
<br>
Nobody wants to buy them, and the merchant price is less than ten platinum so if anybody wants a stylish new robe that isn't all that bad then let me know.<br>
<br>
I'm also on the lookout for tailoring supplies:<br>
<br>
 -- Cursed Clover of Viesar (foraged in Overthere, uncommon drop from succulents in that zone)<br>
 -- Ashweed (foraged in Lavastorm, rare drop from goblin warriors at Hykallen's camp)<br>
 -- Rune of the Cyclone, Words of Burnishing (research components, guess which robes they are used for)<br>
 -- Wing of Xegony (used to research level 49 mage pet, also makes the stylish Robe of Wings with AC 9, DEX 3, STA 3, INT 8, HP 10, mana 5, sv disease 7, sv cold 7.  Bring me some of these and I'll make the robe for you.<br>
 -- Rune of Ellipse (New 50+ research component.  I have only ever seen one of these, but it makes an even better robe.)<br>
<br>
I am also working on studded and reinforced acrylia ( <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.eqtraders.com/secrets/recipes_tailoring_armor.htm">www.eqtraders.com/secrets..._armor.htm</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> ) on the side, so if you are coveting any of that (the studded cloak is quite popular) then send me a tell.<br>
